必须保存准确的记录。

data.enText: able to give completely correct information or to do sth in an exact way

data.chText: 高度精确的电子罗盘仪
精确得误差不超过3毫米
我的表走得不很准。
data.enText: My watch is not very accurate.

data.enText: an accurate throw, shot, weapon, etc. hits or reaches the thing that it was aimed at

data.chText: 文章如实反映了公众的意见。
data.enText: The article accurately reflects public opinion.

data.chText: 你必须准确击球。
data.enText: You need to hit the ball accurately.

data.text: true ♦ right ♦ correct ♦ exact ♦ precise ♦ accurate ♦ spot on

data.chText: 以上各词均指某事确实、真实、确切。
data.enText: These words all describe sth that cannot be doubted as fact and includes no mistakes.

data.chText: 指合乎事实的、确实的、如实的：
data.enText: connected with facts rather than things that have been invented or guessed

data.chText: 下列说法是对还是错？
data.enText: Are the following statements true or false ?

data.chText: 她要走是真的吗？
指正确的、真实的：
data.enText: that is true and cannot be doubted as a fact

data.chText: 我的回答约有一半是正确的。
data.enText: I got about half the answers right.

data.chText: 现在的准确时间是几点？
指准确无误的、正确的：
data.enText: right according to the facts and without any mistakes

data.chText: 这些答案中只有一个是正确的。
data.enText: Only one of the answers is correct.

data.chText: 检查所有这些细节是否准确无误。
data.enText: Check that all the details are correct.

data.chText: 用right还是correct？
correct较right正式，更多用于官方或正式的说明或文件中。
data.enText: Correct is more formal than right and is more likely to be used in official or formal instructions or documents.

data.chText: 指精确的、准确的：
data.enText: [usually before noun] giving all the details correctly

data.chText: 她对袭击者的特征作了精确的描述。
data.enText: She gave an exact description of the attacker.

data.chText: 指准确的、确切的、精确的、明确的：
data.enText: giving all the details clearly and correctly

data.chText: 请准确提供你过去经历的详情。
data.enText: Please give precise details about your previous experience.

data.chText: 指准确无误的、精确的：
任何时候都必须保存准确的记录。
data.enText: Accurate records must be kept at all times.

data.chText: 用exact、precise还是accurate？
accurate与exact和precise一样常用于名词前：
data.enText: Accurate can often be used before a noun in the same way as exact and precise .

data.chText: 准确的记录
上述的词用于连系动词后，尤其在否定句中，侧重点稍有不同。not very exact/precise指缺乏细节；not very accurate指出了细节，但细节有误；precise含明确、确切和准确之义；短语be precise about sth可用于人，指能准确说出某事；exact通常不这样用：
data.enText: When the words are used after a linking verb, there is a slightly different emphasis, especially in negative statements. A description that is not very exact/precise lacks details; a description that is not very accurate gives details, but the details are wrong. Precise includes the idea of being clear and certain as well as correct and can be used to talk about people in the phrase be precise about sth . Exact is not usually used in this way.
She was reasonably exact about the time of the incident.

data.chText: 指完全正确、对极了：
data.enText: [not before noun] ( BrE informal ) exactly right

data.chText: 他的猜测完全正确。

data.enText: It would be true/accurate to say that…

ex.chText: 为了得到准确的销售数据他一宿没睡。
ex.enText: He stayed up all night in order to get the precise sales figures.

ex.chText: 准确地说，这趟火车10点28分开出。
ex.enText: To be precise, the train leaves at 10:28.

synonyms.bx: 强调信息、细节等准确无误的。

ex.chText: 那位老人能向警方准确描述小偷的情况吗？
ex.enText: Was the old man able to give the police an accurate description of the thief?
It is important to keep accurate records.

synonyms.bx: 指报道、描述等符合事实的，也指测量数据、计算结果、记录内容等没有差错的。

ex.enText: an exact description of the attacker

ex.chText: 飞机失事的确切位置还不清楚。
ex.enText: The exact location of the plane crash is still unknown.

synonyms.bx: 指每个细节都正确无误的，多作定语。

tr: conforming exactly or almost exactly to fact or to a standard or performing with total accuracy
(of ideas, images, representations, expressions) characterized by perfect conformity to fact or truth

value.def: Accurate information, measurements, and statistics are correct to a very detailed level. An accurate instrument is able to give you information of this kind.

example.ex: Police have stressed that this is the most accurate description of the killer to date...
example.tran: 警方强调这是迄今对凶手最精确的描述。

example.ex: This may provide a quick and accurate way of monitoring the amount of carbon dioxide in the air...
example.tran: 这也许能提供一个监测空气中二氧化碳含量的既快又准的方法。

example.ex: Quartz timepieces are very accurate, to a minute or two per year.
example.tran: 石英钟表走时非常准，年误差仅为一两分钟。

value.tran: （信息、测量、数据或仪器等）精确的，准确的

example.ex: The test can accurately predict what a bigger explosion would do.
example.tran: 该试验能准确地预测一次更大爆炸的威力。

value.def: An accurate statement or account gives a true or fair judgment of something.

example.ex: I think it may take sometime before we can have an accurate assessment of the damage...
example.tran: 我认为我们对损失作出准确的估算可能需要一段时间。

example.ex: They were accurate in their prediction that he would change her life drastically.
example.tran: 他们预测得没错，他使她的生活发生了翻天覆地的变化。

example.ex: What many people mean by the word 'power' could be more accurately described as 'control'.
example.tran: 多数人所谓的“权力”，其实更确切地说是“控制”。

value.def: You can use accurate to describe the results of someone's actions when they do or copy something correctly or exactly.

example.ex: Marks were given for accurate spelling and punctuation.
example.tran: 因拼写及标点正确而得分。

example.ex: ...his maliciously accurate imitation of Hubert de Burgh.
example.tran: 他对休伯特·德伯格到位的恶搞模仿

value.def: An accurate weapon or throw reaches the exact point or target that it was intended to reach. You can also describe a person as accurate if they fire a weapon or throw something in this way.

example.ex: The pilots, however, were not as accurate as they should be.
example.tran: 然而飞行员并不像他们该达到的水平那样精准。

value.tran: （武器、投掷）精准的；（人）射击（或投掷）准的

example.ex: ...the technology to aim bombs accurately from aircraft.
